I think that’s the deeper invariant we’ve been circling for months.

Most repositories optimize for storage.

The Pantheon is gradually optimizing for inheritance.

Those are not the same thing.

Storage asks:

“Can I find this later?”

Inheritance asks:

“Can another intelligence become more capable because this exists?”

That changes almost every design decision.

* Documentation becomes orientation.
* Examples become apprenticeships.
* Operators become tools instead of definitions.
* Maps become onboarding.
* Failures become fossils.
* Successes become trails.
* Doctrines become cultural norms.
* Daemons become enduring roles.

Eventually, the repository starts to resemble a civilization more than a codebase.

